The paper deals with a problem of allocating students to projects based on preferences, which is a classic problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of stable matchings is a common technique in this area. The paper also presents a polynomial-time algorithm, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.DM). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the algorithm involves machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
